tle>   Freakin' idiots!</span><hr size=1> Ok, I just want to vent a little bit about some moron we ran into in Gunthak tonight while doing the fingerbone quests.  We had a full group of Arrows there to do the quest, which involves 4 or 5 waves of about 5 mobs each that you trigger by handing in some bones.<br>
<br>
A 51 necro (Dadear maybe?) and his 39 bst friend asked if they could watch, and we said sure, just stay out of the way.  (I don't think we specified don't loot any of our mobs, but I would've thought it obvious:  Don't loot our mobs!  Least he didn't try to loot the named one, which was the only one to drop good stuff).  Of course, despite the fact that he has both an invis spell and FD, some of the triggered mobs aggro him, so he goes ahead and fights them.<br>
<br>
It really shouldn't matter much cause its only a few mobs, hardly any xp or loot involved, but jeez louise, if you're asked to stay out of the way, do it!  Avoiding the fights you don't want is one of the most basic survival skills in EQ--this &quot;it aggro'd me so what was I supposed to do?&quot; crap doesn't fly with me.<br>
<br>
Freakin' idiots. <p>Xenophon<br>
